1:19:59.633 --> 1:20:03.333
♪ Merry Christmas to all

1:20:03.467 --> 1:20:08.800
♪ And a Happy New Year

1:20:26.567 --> 1:20:28.967
Come on.
Come on, you guys.

1:20:32.567 --> 1:20:34.500
You were incredible, Ellie.

1:20:34.633 --> 1:20:36.300
That was so much fun!

1:20:36.433 --> 1:20:38.300
Oh, look. Mom and Dad.

1:20:39.266 --> 1:20:40.133
You're looking for my mom?

1:20:40.266 --> 1:20:41.133
- Yeah.
- This way.

1:20:41.266 --> 1:20:42.800
- You were amazing.
- Thanks!

1:20:42.934 --> 1:20:44.000
Mom, look who I found.

1:20:44.133 --> 1:20:45.767
Oh! Hi.

1:20:45.900 --> 1:20:48.467
Well, some date
I turned out to be, huh?

1:20:48.600 --> 1:20:49.767
Oh, so it was a date?

1:20:49.900 --> 1:20:51.300
Wasn't she great?

1:20:51.433 --> 1:20:53.100
I just got the whole story!

1:20:53.233 --> 1:20:55.266
She was up all night,
rehearsing with Josh.

1:20:55.400 --> 1:20:56.767
Well, Josh didn't call
and ask me to sing

1:20:56.900 --> 1:20:58.633
until after Sara
went to bed.

1:20:58.767 --> 1:21:01.734
And then, well, he still
had to do the arrangements

1:21:01.867 --> 1:21:03.433
and print the programs--
he was up all night.

1:21:04.867 --> 1:21:06.066
That must be his agent.

1:21:06.200 --> 1:21:08.066
Oh, no. That's just a friend.

1:21:08.200 --> 1:21:11.200
Josh called off his agent
once he convinced Anna to sing.

1:21:12.467 --> 1:21:13.834
Actually, George, you should
come meet the guy.

1:21:13.967 --> 1:21:16.867
He needs someone to renovate
a new duplex he bought.

1:21:17.000 --> 1:21:18.700
Come on.
Go meet the guy.

1:21:18.834 --> 1:21:20.100
Come on.

1:21:22.000 --> 1:21:24.633
You are very good
at keeping secrets.

1:21:24.767 --> 1:21:26.667
Well, that was Josh's idea.

1:21:26.800 --> 1:21:30.200
He wanted this moment
to be as memorable for you

1:21:30.333 --> 1:21:32.133
as it was for me.

1:21:32.266 --> 1:21:34.667
I didn't think anyone
would get you to sing again.

1:21:34.800 --> 1:21:36.166
Hmm. Neither did I.

1:21:36.300 --> 1:21:37.333
But Josh...

1:21:37.467 --> 1:21:38.467
and George...

1:21:39.667 --> 1:21:40.533
...sometimes,
you're lucky enough

1:21:40.667 --> 1:21:42.834
to find people
who care enough about you

1:21:42.967 --> 1:21:45.667
to show you what you've been
blind to all along.

1:21:45.800 --> 1:21:47.333
Sweetheart.

1:21:47.467 --> 1:21:50.033
I never want you
to stop dreaming.

1:21:50.166 --> 1:21:51.400
Come here.

1:21:53.300 --> 1:21:55.000
What a night!

1:21:59.133 --> 1:22:01.734
Wouldn't that be pretty
in the bay window at the condo?

1:22:01.867 --> 1:22:02.900
Absolutely.
What better way

1:22:03.033 --> 1:22:05.467
to celebrate Christmas
in your new home?

1:22:05.600 --> 1:22:07.533
Our new home!

1:22:08.600 --> 1:22:09.734
Time to make
some new traditions.

1:22:09.867 --> 1:22:12.633
All right. Anything else
you want me to take?

1:22:12.767 --> 1:22:16.066
Well, if there's enough room,
you could take me.

1:22:16.200 --> 1:22:17.200
Oh!

1:22:17.333 --> 1:22:18.734
Just happen to have a space.

1:22:18.867 --> 1:22:20.166
Right next to me.

1:22:21.367 --> 1:22:23.033
- Goodnight, sweetheart.
- Goodnight.

1:22:38.734 --> 1:22:40.734
You were glowing tonight.

1:22:40.867 --> 1:22:42.000
Likewise.

1:22:43.066 --> 1:22:44.734
It almost felt like
old times, huh?

1:22:44.867 --> 1:22:46.400
We're timeless.

1:22:47.734 --> 1:22:48.767
Yeah, well.

1:22:50.533 --> 1:22:53.066
And here I thought
you could manage anything.

1:22:54.200 --> 1:22:56.433
Story of a producer's life, right?

1:22:56.567 --> 1:22:59.066
Make a clean sweep
and start all over.

1:22:59.200 --> 1:23:01.033
Mm.

1:23:01.166 --> 1:23:03.800
Speaking of "start over"...

1:23:04.667 --> 1:23:07.300
I've been thinking about that.

1:23:07.433 --> 1:23:09.333
It has its advantages.

1:23:09.467 --> 1:23:11.300
Yeah.

1:23:11.433 --> 1:23:15.467
And I'm licensed
to practice law in four states,

1:23:15.600 --> 1:23:18.700
so I could pretty much
do that from anywhere.

1:23:18.834 --> 1:23:20.533
But music...

1:23:20.667 --> 1:23:24.200
I can only want do that
in one place...

1:23:24.333 --> 1:23:25.633
with one person.

1:23:26.967 --> 1:23:28.066
Really?

1:23:29.100 --> 1:23:30.033
Just a day ago,

1:23:30.166 --> 1:23:31.867
you were off to a big
law firm gala in New York

1:23:32.000 --> 1:23:33.233
for New Year's.

1:23:34.500 --> 1:23:36.567
My plans changed.

1:23:38.000 --> 1:23:40.533
Don't you ever
want to make partner?

1:23:42.166 --> 1:23:45.066
I already have a partner.

1:23:50.266 --> 1:23:52.433
And I already have
a ticket to New York.

1:23:53.500 --> 1:23:55.133
♪ I'll be coming home

1:23:55.266 --> 1:23:58.166
♪ I'll be there for Christmas

1:23:58.300 --> 1:24:00.700
♪ Christmas, baby

1:24:00.834 --> 1:24:02.433
♪ So keep the light on...

1:24:02.567 --> 1:24:05.200
♪ Keep the light on for me

1:24:05.333 --> 1:24:07.233
♪ It's Christmas, baby...

1:24:07.367 --> 1:24:09.767
- Merry Christmas.
- Merry Christmas.

